1
00:00:11,144 --> 00:00:15,046
[ Young Sydney ]                
WHAT ARE YOU SEEING, JAROD?     
[ Young Jarod ] I'M NOT SURE.   


2
00:00:15,115 --> 00:00:19,818
COME ON, THINK.                 
THINK, JAROD.                   


3
00:00:22,923 --> 00:00:25,423
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?              


4
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:28,193
                THESE PEOPLE,   


5
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:30,195
                SOME ARE ANGRY, 


6
00:00:30,263 --> 00:00:32,364
                SOME ARE SAD.   


7
00:00:32,432 --> 00:00:35,133
- BUT ALL FOR THE SAME REASON.  
- AND THAT IS?                  


8
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:38,203
        THEIR TRUST HAS BEEN    
        VIOLATED, SYDNEY...     


9
00:00:39,339 --> 00:00:41,472
    BY SOMEONE THEY LOOK UP TO. 


10
00:00:43,643 --> 00:00:48,447
        AND NOW,                
        THEY CAN'T TRUST HIM.   


11
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:06,631
<i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>              


12
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:08,934
[ Shouting, Indistinct ]        


13
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:12,604
<i>CAPTAIN HARRIGAN.</i>               
                ARE WE CLEAR?   


14
00:01:12,673 --> 00:01:15,306
O'LEARY'S STILL IN THERE.       


15
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:18,310
    O'LEARY, GET THE HELL OUT.  
    THAT PLACE IS GONE.         


16
00:01:18,379 --> 00:01:20,478
    [ Crying ]                  


17
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:29,021
        O'LEARY, REPORT.        


18
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:31,289
    -<i> WHAT THE HELL</i>             
     <i> ARE YOU DOING IN THERE?</i>   
    - MOMMY, WHERE ARE YOU?     


19
00:01:31,358 --> 00:01:33,291
        <i> SOMEBODY HELP ME.</i>      


20
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:38,530
IT'S OKAY.                      
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.      


21
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:40,799
DAMN IT, O'LEARY.               
GET THE HELL OUT OF THERE, NOW. 


22
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:44,869
        SIR.                    


23
00:01:49,176 --> 00:01:52,210
        THAT'S MY BABY!         
         THAT'S MY BABY!        


24
00:01:55,883 --> 00:01:58,683
            <i> THAT'S MY BABY!</i>    
             <i> THAT'S MY BABY!</i>   


25
00:01:59,686 --> 00:02:03,354
                GAIL. OH, GAIL. 


26
00:02:03,423 --> 00:02:05,490
                    THANK YOU.  


27
00:02:05,559 --> 00:02:08,326
JUST DOING MY JOB, MA'AM.       


28
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:12,830
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


29
00:03:02,483 --> 00:03:05,183
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>SO MR. RAINES LOANED HIM TO US?</i> 


30
00:03:05,252 --> 00:03:07,252
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>YES, MISS PARKER.</i>               


31
00:03:11,758 --> 00:03:13,858
        <i> YOU WANNA TELL ME WHY?</i> 


32
00:03:13,927 --> 00:03:18,463
BEAR IN MIND THAT JAROD'S       
MODUS OPERANDI THUS FAR...      


33
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:20,465
HAS BEEN TO COLLECT             
NEWSPAPER STORIES.              


34
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:22,467
        SO IF WE CAN ESTABLISH  
        A CORRELATION...        


35
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:25,003
    BETWEEN HIS SELECTION       
    PROCESS AND HIS MOVEMENTS,  


36
00:03:25,072 --> 00:03:28,740
WE MAY BE ABLE TO PREDICT       
HIS NEXT MOVE BY SCANNING       
THE LOCAL AND NATIONAL PRESS... 


37
00:03:28,809 --> 00:03:31,143
        FOR STORIES             
        WHICH MAY INTEREST HIM. 


38
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:34,712
AND COUSIN IT                   
IS YOUR MAN FOR THE JOB?        


39
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:38,950
<i>PLEASE DON'T TRIVIALIZE THIS,</i>   
<i>MISS PARKER.</i>                    


40
00:03:39,019 --> 00:03:43,722
HIS NAME IS ANGELO.             
HE'S VERY SPECIAL.              


41
00:03:47,461 --> 00:03:49,861
            OH, I CAN SEE THAT. 


42
00:03:58,138 --> 00:04:01,806
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]      


43
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:05,576
MAN, JAROD. YOU BARELY          
GET YOUR BOOTS UNPACKED,        
YOU'RE ALREADY KING OF THE HILL.


44
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:08,046
            [ Chuckles ]        
YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT             
THAT PLACE WAS A GONER.         


45
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:10,748
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU JUST WALKED 
RIGHT THROUGH THAT INFERNO.     


46
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:13,785
    WELL, I WOULDN'T RECOMMEND  
    TRYING IT AT HOME.          


47
00:04:13,853 --> 00:04:16,554
    - ACTUALLY,                 
      IT'S SAFER ON THE JOB.    
    - SAFER?                    


48
00:04:16,623 --> 00:04:19,925
<i>68.6% OF YOUR SERIOUS</i>           
<i>INJURIES OCCUR AT HOME.</i>         


49
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:23,461
YOU RUN THE NUMBERS, IT'S       
A BIGGER RISK TAKING A BATH     
THAN IT IS FIGHTING A FIRE.     


50
00:04:23,530 --> 00:04:26,631
- THE TRUTH IS, I WAS JUST      
  FOLLOWING THE EXIT SIGNS.     
- [ Chuckles ]                  


51
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,833
    HEY, CAN YOU SHOW ME        
    WHERE I CAN STOW THIS GEAR? 


52
00:04:28,902 --> 00:04:31,068
YEAH, FOLLOW ME.                


53
00:04:31,137 --> 00:04:34,172
<i>YOU TAKE ANY LOCKER YOU WANT.</i>   
<i>JUST MAKE SURE IT DOESN'T</i>       
<i>HAVE A NAME ON IT.</i>              


54
00:04:36,676 --> 00:04:38,843
        ANY ONE BUT THIS ONE.   
I'M SORRY.                      
I DIDN'T KNOW--                 


55
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:40,812
LIEUTENANT GLEASON?             


56
00:04:40,881 --> 00:04:43,715
    SORRY, MAN.                 
    I SHOULD HAVE WARNED YOU.   


57
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:46,284
THAT'S TAMARA COPELAND'S LOCKER.


58
00:04:46,353 --> 00:04:49,921
THE FIREFIGHTER                 
THAT WAS KILLED.                
                    MM-HMM.     


59
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:52,424
    SHE AND GLEASON WERE TIGHT. 


60
00:04:52,493 --> 00:04:55,994
    I GUESS YOU COMING HERE     
    KIND OF, YOU KNOW,          
    CLOSES THE DOOR ON ALL THAT.


61
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:59,831
        OR OPENS A WOUND.       
<i>JAROD,</i>                          
<i>THERE YOU ARE.</i>                  


62
00:05:01,201 --> 00:05:03,334
ONE DAY ON THE JOB WITH US...   


63
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:06,204
<i>AND YOU'RE KICKING ASS</i>          
<i>LIKE A 20-YEAR VETERAN.</i>         


64
00:05:06,273 --> 00:05:10,842
I WANT YOU TO TAKE A GOOD LOOK  
AT THIS GUY, ROY. GUTS, BRAINS  
AND A TOUCH OF THE CRAZIES.     


65
00:05:10,911 --> 00:05:13,445
<i>THAT'S WHAT THE FIGHTING 16th</i>   
<i>IS ALL ABOUT.</i>                   


66
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:16,948
LISTEN, JAROD. THE REPORTERS    
ARE READY TO GET UP CLOSE       
AND PERSONAL WITH YOU.          


67
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:21,453
        UH, SIR, I DON'T WANT   
        ANY PUBLICITY.          


68
00:05:21,522 --> 00:05:26,224
JAROD, YOU ARE NOW              
A MEMBER OF THE BEST DAMN       
FIRE-FIGHTING UNIT IN THIS CITY.


69
00:05:26,293 --> 00:05:28,226
YOU SHOULD BE PROUD OF THAT.    


70
00:05:28,295 --> 00:05:30,295
BESIDES, IT'S GOOD FOR THE TEAM.


71
00:05:30,363 --> 00:05:32,964
                YES, SIR.       


72
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:34,966
SMILE PRETTY.                   


73
00:05:39,973 --> 00:05:43,107
            ♪♪ [ Cocktail ]     


74
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:52,117
<i>AND HOW LONG ARE WE GOING TO</i>    
<i>HAVE TO WAIT UNTIL YOUR SAVANT</i>  
<i>ZEROES IN ON JAROD'S LOCATION?</i>  


75
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:55,454
ANGELO IS NOT A SAVANT,         
MISS PARKER.                    


76
00:05:55,522 --> 00:06:00,358
ACTUALLY, WE DON'T HAVE         
A CLASSIFICATION FOR WHAT HE IS.


77
00:06:00,427 --> 00:06:03,161
BUT THINK OF HIM LIKE           
A SPONGE, IF YOU WILL.          


78
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,163
<i>HE HAS NO PERSONALITY</i>           
<i>OF HIS OWN,</i>                     


79
00:06:05,232 --> 00:06:09,401
<i>BUT HE CAN ABSORB</i>               
<i>THE PERSONALITY DATA</i>            
<i>THAT WE GIVE HIM.</i>               


80
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:12,336
AND HE HAS READ EVERY           
SCRAP WE HAVE ON JAROD.         


81
00:06:12,405 --> 00:06:16,007
SO NOW HE'S ANOTHER PRETENDER?  
<i>NO.</i>                             


82
00:06:16,076 --> 00:06:19,945
HE COULD NEVER MAKE             
A MORAL JUDGMENT OF HIS OWN.    


83
00:06:21,314 --> 00:06:23,247
ALSO, HE WOULD NEVER RUN AWAY.  


84
00:06:23,316 --> 00:06:26,417
WHERE HAVE I HEARD THAT BEFORE? 


85
00:06:28,254 --> 00:06:31,723
                        PARKER? 
            MICHAEL.            


86
00:06:31,792 --> 00:06:33,724
                    COME HERE.  


87
00:06:33,794 --> 00:06:37,562
        - I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS. 
          HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN? 
        - TOO LONG.             


88
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:40,131
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?        
            SHORT BUSINESS TRIP.


89
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:42,934
I'M A SALES REP FOR             
A PHARMACEUTICAL COMPANY NOW.   


90
00:06:43,003 --> 00:06:45,937
THIS IS PART OF MY TERRITORY.   
WHAT ABOUT YOU?                 


91
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:49,607
I, UH, HAVE A MID-LEVEL         
POSITION WITH A LOCAL FIRM,     


92
00:06:49,676 --> 00:06:52,744
        <i> NOTHING VERY EXCITING,</i> 
        <i> I'M AFRAID.</i>            


93
00:06:52,813 --> 00:06:55,313
        I CANNOT GET OVER       
        HOW TERRIFIC YOU LOOK.  


94
00:06:55,381 --> 00:06:57,548
DESPITE THE LACK OF GOOD SEX.   


95
00:06:59,653 --> 00:07:01,386
[ Clears Throat ]               


96
00:07:01,455 --> 00:07:03,721
    MICHAEL PATRICK,            
    THIS IS SYDNEY,             


97
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,891
                <i> MY ASSISTANT.</i>  


98
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:08,426
            - MICHAEL.          
            - SYDNEY.           


99
00:07:08,495 --> 00:07:11,495
        ANYWAY, I WOULD         
        ASK YOU TO JOIN ME      
        FOR A DRINK AT THE BAR, 


100
00:07:11,565 --> 00:07:14,632
            BUT I CAN SEE THAT  
            YOU'RE BOTH, UH--   
OH, SYDNEY WAS JUST LEAVING.    


101
00:07:14,701 --> 00:07:19,437
YES, APPARENTLY, SYDNEY         
WAS JUST ABOUT TO LEAVE.        


102
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:25,443
                    OH, GREAT.  


103
00:07:25,512 --> 00:07:27,511
            I'LL BE AT THE BAR. 


104
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:35,487
    SEE YOU AT THE OFFICE, SYD. 


105
00:07:38,391 --> 00:07:41,126
            LET'S SEE.          
            I'M DOING MY NAILS, 


106
00:07:41,195 --> 00:07:46,631
<i>WASHING MY HAIR,</i>                
<i>SMOKING A CIGARETTE.</i>            


107
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:49,667
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>AND YOU'RE TALKING TO YOURSELF.</i> 


108
00:07:49,736 --> 00:07:53,905
YEAH, SO WHAT?                  
THAT'S WHAT ARSON               
INVESTIGATORS DO.               


109
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:56,207
            JAROD O'LEARY.      
            I'M WITH THE 16th.  


110
00:07:56,276 --> 00:08:00,278
YEAH, I HEARD ALL ABOUT YOU.    
YOU'RE THE GUY WHO SAVED THE    
LITTLE GIRL IN THIS BUILDING.   


111
00:08:00,347 --> 00:08:03,013
HARRIGAN MUST BE                
DOING BACKFLIPS OVER YOU.       


112
00:08:03,082 --> 00:08:06,184
    JOHN ZIMMERMAN.             
        OH, I KNOW WHO YOU ARE. 


113
00:08:06,252 --> 00:08:09,387
    YOU CAUGHT                  
    THE NORTH HILLS ARSONIST,   
    PRETTY IMPRESSIVE WORK.     


114
00:08:09,456 --> 00:08:12,023
YEAH, WELL,                     
IT DIDN'T GET ME ANY DATES.     


115
00:08:13,226 --> 00:08:16,561
IT'S GLORY BOYS LIKE YOU        
THAT GET ALL THE PLAY.          


116
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:19,464
    I BET YOU COULD             
    TELL ME SOME TALES, HUH?    


117
00:08:19,532 --> 00:08:23,634
WELL, I DO KNOW THIS ONE        
ABOUT THIS LITTLE MONKEY        
AND THIS MAN IN THE YELLOW HAT. 


118
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:27,239
    [ Chuckles ]                
    YEAH, I CAN TAKE A HINT.    


119
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:31,642
<i>NOBODY WANTS</i>                    
<i>TO TALK TO GUYS LIKE ME,</i>        
<i>UNLESS THERE'S A FIRE.</i>          


120
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:33,912
        THEN THERE'S QUESTIONS, 
        NOTHING BUT QUESTIONS.  


121
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:35,913
        IF YOU'RE SO UNHAPPY,   
        WHY DID YOU PICK        
        THIS LINE OF WORK?      


122
00:08:35,983 --> 00:08:37,715
<i>I DIDN'T HAVE</i>                   
<i>ANY CHOICE, REALLY.</i>             


123
00:08:37,784 --> 00:08:42,119
    MOST GUYS WHO WANNA BE      
    THIS CLOSE TO A FIRE,       


124
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:45,056
    THEY EITHER SET 'EM         
    OR FIGHT 'EM.               


125
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:48,093
I FALL IN THE LATTER CATEGORY.  
[ Groans ]                      


126
00:08:48,161 --> 00:08:51,162
                ARE YOU OKAY?   
        OH, BUM KNEE.           


127
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:53,497
        SPORTS INJURY?          


128
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:55,900
IS THAT SOME KIND OF A JOKE?    


129
00:08:55,969 --> 00:08:59,370
        <i> I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING.</i>


130
00:08:59,439 --> 00:09:02,073
    - DO YOU MIND IF I          
      TAKE A STAB AT THIS?      
    - FEEL FREE.                


131
00:09:04,443 --> 00:09:07,646
    WELL, WE KNOW THAT          
    THE OCCUPANT WAS A SMOKER.  


132
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:11,448
SHE WAS SMOKING A CIGARETTE,    
DOING HER NAILS.                


133
00:09:11,517 --> 00:09:14,952
    <i> SO MY GUESS WOULD BE</i>       
    <i> THAT SHE FELL ASLEEP,</i>      
    <i> DROPPED THE CIGARETTE AND--</i>


134
00:09:15,021 --> 00:09:18,523
        [ Imitates Blast ]      
        IGNITED THE FLUIDS.     
<i>THAT'S GOOD.</i>                    


135
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:21,993
REAL GOOD.                      
ALSO WRONG.                     


136
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,762
<i>ELECTRICAL FIRE.</i>                
        REALLY?                 
        WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE? 


137
00:09:24,831 --> 00:09:28,133
WELL, SEE, THE OUTLET           
WAS OVERLOADED.                 


138
00:09:28,201 --> 00:09:31,035
<i>THE BURNS ARE MOSTLY</i>            
<i>CONCENTRATED ON THE WALLS.</i>      


139
00:09:31,104 --> 00:09:33,705
<i>THE FINGERNAIL POLISH FLUID</i>     
<i>IGNITED MUCH LATER.</i>             


140
00:09:36,877 --> 00:09:39,844
OH, ANOTHER NEEDLESS            
CATASTROPHE SOLVED.             


141
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:43,081
                    IMPRESSIVE. 
        EH.                     


142
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:48,386
YOU KNOW,                       
THE SADDEST THING IS...         
                        HMM?    


143
00:09:48,455 --> 00:09:51,088
<i>THIS SINGED MATTRESS.</i>           


144
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:53,324
THIS IS THE CLOSEST             
I GET TO SEX.                   


145
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:14,311
        LONG LUNCH, MISS PARKER.


146
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:16,313
NOT BORING FOR ONCE.            


147
00:10:16,382 --> 00:10:19,050
ANY PROGRESS?                   
    WELL, SLOW BUT STEADY.      


148
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,285
    ALTHOUGH I CAN SAY          
    WITH 90% CERTAINTY...       


149
00:10:21,354 --> 00:10:24,756
    THAT JAROD IS DUE           
    TO LAND SOMEWHERE EAST      
    OF THE MISSISSIPPI.         


150
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:27,658
<i>ANGELO HAS ELIMINATED</i>           
<i>EVERYTHING WEST OF THAT.</i>        


151
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:30,128
WE ARE DEFINITELY CLOSING IN.   


152
00:10:30,197 --> 00:10:32,530
YOU DON'T GET OUT MUCH,         
DO YOU, BROOTS?                 


153
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:34,833
PAGE ME IF YOU HAVE             
A BREAKTHROUGH.                 


154
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:37,835
            WHERE WILL YOU BE?  
        OUT.                    


155
00:10:40,507 --> 00:10:42,673
WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?        


156
00:10:42,742 --> 00:10:46,211
IT APPEARS MISS PARKER          
HAS TAKEN A SUDDEN INTEREST...  


157
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:49,780
IN THE PHARMACEUTICAL INDUSTRY. 


158
00:10:53,086 --> 00:10:55,787
        [ Growling ]            


159
00:10:55,856 --> 00:10:57,788
            [ Growling ]        


160
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:06,130
<i>[ Roy ]</i>                         
<i>DON'T WORRY.</i>                    
<i>EMBER GROWLS AT ALL STRANGERS.</i>  


161
00:11:06,198 --> 00:11:10,068
        HOW LONG DO I GOTTA KEEP
        STIRRING THIS MESS?     
    JUST UNTIL IT COAGULATES.   


162
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:13,838
    THAT'S A GOOD WORD FOR IT.  


163
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:17,141
    -<i> HE THINKS YOU'RE A DOG.</i>   
    - HE DOES?                  


164
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:20,311
YEAH, YOU'RE A STRANGER         
IN THIS PLACE. HE'S JUST        
TRYING TO ESTABLISH DOMINANCE.  


165
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,313
<i>REALLY?</i>                         
            WHAT, YOU NEVER HAD 
            A DOG BEFORE?       


166
00:11:22,382 --> 00:11:26,384
        NO. I DID DRIVE A CHIMP 
        THROUGH THE AMAZON ONCE.


167
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:28,686
            [ Chuckles ]        


168
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:33,391
        - HERE YOU GO.          
        - [ Whining ]           


169
00:11:33,459 --> 00:11:36,928
    HE'LL LOVE YOU IN NO TIME.  
    DOGS ARE AMAZINGLY          
    LOYAL CREATURES.            


170
00:11:36,996 --> 00:11:39,664
    YOU KEEP THEIR BELLIES FULL,
    THEY'LL DO ANYTHING YOU ASK.


171
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:43,300
        QUIT SCREWIN' AROUND    
        WITH THAT STUPID MUTT.  
        WE'RE WAITING FOR LUNCH.


172
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,302
    COMING RIGHT UP, SIR.       


173
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,742
    NOW WE KNOW WHY             
    YOU HAD TO TRANSFER         
    FROM YOUR LAST ASSIGNMENT.  


174
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:01,753
[ Jarod ]                       
BON APPÉTIT.                    
            WHAT IS THIS SLOP?  


175
00:12:01,821 --> 00:12:04,455
IT'S OPTIMIZED                  
NUTRITIONAL SUPPLEMENT.         


176
00:12:04,524 --> 00:12:08,426
<i>HEARTS OF PALM, WHEAT GRASS AND</i> 
<i>ASPARAGUS STEWED WITH TOMATO.</i>   


177
00:12:08,494 --> 00:12:10,461
<i>[ Disapproving Chatter ]</i>        


178
00:12:12,765 --> 00:12:15,800
    - I GREW UP ON THIS STUFF.  
    - THREW UP IS MORE LIKE IT. 


179
00:12:15,869 --> 00:12:19,637
            <i> [ Clicking Tongue ]</i>
[ Whining ]                     


180
00:12:19,705 --> 00:12:23,574
<i>PEOPLE, THERE'S ONLY ONE THING</i>  
<i>THAT CAN SAVE THIS DISASTER.</i>    


181
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:26,811
                INSTA-CHEEZ!    


182
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:38,956
HAVEN'T HAD A DECENT MEAL       
AROUND HERE SINCE COPELAND DIED.


183
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:11,015
        [ No Audible Dialogue ] 


184
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:38,175
[ Miss Parker ]                 
SO HE'S ON THE FLOOR.           
I'M ON TOP OF HIM.              


185
00:14:38,244 --> 00:14:41,645
WE'RE BOTH SPENT,               
COVERED IN SWEAT.               


186
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:44,348
    AND YOU'RE STILL DOING THIS?


187
00:14:44,417 --> 00:14:47,151
AT LEAST THREE TIMES A WEEK.    


188
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:50,821
    ISN'T IT HARD TO MAINTAIN   
    THAT LEVEL OF INTENSITY?    


189
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:53,291
NOT IF YOU'RE DOING IT RIGHT.   


190
00:14:57,464 --> 00:15:00,965
<i>HMM, YOU'RE NOT DOING IT</i>        
<i>AT ALL, ARE YOU?</i>                


191
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:03,367
            <i> NO, TRUTH IS...</i>    


192
00:15:03,436 --> 00:15:06,103
I GAVE UP FENCING AFTER COLLEGE.


193
00:15:06,172 --> 00:15:12,043
        BESIDES, I NEVER        
        FOUND AN OPPONENT       
        AS FORMIDABLE AS YOU.   


194
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:14,879
    NEVER WILL.                 


195
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:19,083
            [ Chuckles ]        


196
00:15:20,153 --> 00:15:22,419
        YOU STILL HAVE          
        THAT LOOK IN YOUR EYE-- 


197
00:15:23,556 --> 00:15:28,058
            <i> HALF INVITATION,</i>   
            <i> HALF INTIMIDATION.</i> 


198
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:30,728
SO WHICH DO YOU WANT?           


199
00:15:30,797 --> 00:15:33,364
            [ Chuckles ]        


200
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:35,366
    DON'T TEMPT ME, PARKER.     


201
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:38,035
    [ Chuckles ]                
    TOO LATE.                   


202
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:45,509
        UH, CHECK, PLEASE.      


203
00:16:00,727 --> 00:16:04,729
"AEROSOL CHEESE-LIKE            
 IMITATION FOOD PRODUCT."       


204
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:07,465
        OFFICIAL FOOD           
        OF THE FIGHTING 16th.   


205
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:10,534
ACCORDING TO THESE INGREDIENTS, 
THERE'S ABSOLUTELY NO           
NUTRITIONAL VALUE.              


206
00:16:10,603 --> 00:16:14,805
            HEY, TASTES GREAT,  
            AND IT MAKES ME     
            SLEEP LIKE A BABY.  


207
00:16:14,874 --> 00:16:17,207
        WELL, I DOUBT           
        I'M GOING TO BE GETTING 
        MUCH SLEEP AROUND HERE. 


208
00:16:17,276 --> 00:16:19,844
OH, THE BEDS ARE PATHETIC,      
I KNOW. YOU'LL GET USED TO IT.  


209
00:16:19,913 --> 00:16:22,413
NO, I MEAN, I'VE BEEN GOING OVER
SOME OF THESE OLD RECORDS.      


210
00:16:22,482 --> 00:16:25,650
        BOY, YOU GUYS ARE GOOD. 
            <i> 92% KNOCKDOWN RATE.</i>


211
00:16:25,719 --> 00:16:28,586
THAT MAKES US THE MOST          
EFFICIENT COMPANY IN THE CITY.  


212
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,255
    I JUST HOPE I CAN           
    LIVE UP TO YOUR STANDARDS.  
WELL.                           


213
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:34,258
YOU FOLLOW HARRIGAN,            
YOU'LL BE FINE.                 


214
00:16:34,327 --> 00:16:36,727
I WATCHED HIM LEAD              
A RESPONSE WITH ONE PUMPER.     


215
00:16:36,796 --> 00:16:39,630
HE PUT OUT A SIX-ALARM FIRE     
BEFORE THE OTHER FIVE           
EVEN GOT THERE.                 


216
00:16:39,699 --> 00:16:42,300
            SOUNDS LIKE         
            HE TAKES A PRETTY   
            AGGRESSIVE APPROACH.


217
00:16:43,636 --> 00:16:46,571
                EXCEPT FOR THESE
                WAREHOUSE FIRES.


218
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:49,807
    THE COMPANY ARRIVED         
    BEFORE THE STRUCTURES       
    WERE COMPLETELY ENGULFED.   


219
00:16:49,876 --> 00:16:53,110
        YET EACH TIME, HARRIGAN 
        PULLED THE TEAM BACK.   


220
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:57,915
    - YEAH, THEY WERE N.W.S.'s. 
    - N.W.S.?                   


221
00:16:57,983 --> 00:17:02,353
<i>NOT WORTH SAVING.</i>               
<i>HARRIGAN DECIDED THEY WERE</i>      
<i>TOO VOLATILE TO RISK HIS MEN.</i>   


222
00:17:02,422 --> 00:17:04,788
    LIVE TO FIGHT ANOTHER DAY.  


223
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:08,092
<i>RIGHT. LOOK, JAROD,</i>             
<i>YOU'RE GONNA FIT IN FINE HERE.</i>  


224
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:13,163
IT'S LIKE I SAID--              
YOU TRUST HARRIGAN'S LEAD,      
HE'LL TAKE CARE OF US.          


225
00:17:15,735 --> 00:17:17,935
        <i> [ Michael ]</i>            
        <i> NICE PLACE</i>             
        <i> YOU GOT HERE, PARKER.</i>  


226
00:17:18,003 --> 00:17:21,004
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>HOW DO YOU KNOW? YOU HAVEN'T</i>    
<i>EVEN SEEN THE BEDROOM YET.</i>      


227
00:17:21,073 --> 00:17:23,207
            <i> AND AT THIS RATE,</i>  
            <i> I NEVER WILL.</i>      


228
00:17:27,914 --> 00:17:31,749
HOW ABOUT A DRINK?              
    DON'T TELL ME YOU'RE TIRED. 


229
00:17:31,818 --> 00:17:34,451
I'M JUST GETTING WARM.          


230
00:17:36,956 --> 00:17:40,124
        I'LL DEFINITELY         
        BE WANTING THAT DRINK.  


231
00:17:48,168 --> 00:17:53,771
    I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU LET     
    ALL THIS ENERGY GO TO WASTE 
    ON A SALES JOB.             


232
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,773
DON'T FORGET,                   


233
00:17:55,842 --> 00:17:59,343
IF IT WEREN'T FOR THAT JOB,     
I WOULDN'T BE HERE.             


234
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:02,479
            WHEN DO YOU LEAVE?  


235
00:18:02,548 --> 00:18:04,749
I THOUGHT YOU WEREN'T           
DONE WITH ME.                   


236
00:18:08,121 --> 00:18:10,988
I'LL BE HERE FOR...             


237
00:18:13,159 --> 00:18:15,325
TWO DAYS.                       


238
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:17,327
                THEN LET'S NOT  
                WASTE ANY TIME. 


239
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:34,878
HERE WE ARE, GENTLEMEN.         
EAT IN GOOD HEALTH.             


240
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:36,713
        YEAH.                   
                        <i> THANKS.</i>


241
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,949
                <i> HEY, HANDSOME.</i> 


242
00:18:39,018 --> 00:18:40,951
NANCY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE? 


243
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:43,286
    I WAS IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.  
    THOUGHT I'D DROP OFF        
    YOUR WORK SHIRTS.           


244
00:18:43,355 --> 00:18:45,623
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.      
            I KNOW. I WANT TO.  


245
00:18:45,692 --> 00:18:47,624
            BUSINESS LOOKS GOOD.


246
00:18:47,694 --> 00:18:51,695
OH, SINCE BREAKFAST             
THIS MORNING, ON TOP OF WHICH,  
MANNY CALLS IN SICK.            


247
00:18:51,764 --> 00:18:53,965
            MANNY IS SICK?      
            WELL, WHO'S COOKING?


248
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:56,767
<i>HEY, HERB.</i>                      


249
00:18:56,836 --> 00:18:59,036
WHAT SHOULD I DO                
WITH THESE BALLS OF MEAT?       


250
00:18:59,105 --> 00:19:02,372
I THINK YOU TWO KNOW EACH OTHER.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THE MEATBALLS,


251
00:19:02,441 --> 00:19:05,643
    <i> IF YOU'LL FINISH</i>           
    <i> CLEANING UP, OKAY, JAROD?</i>  
        SURE.                   


252
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:10,247
CAREFUL, IT'S HOT.              
        OKAY, THANKS.           


253
00:19:13,752 --> 00:19:15,686
        GREAT GUY.              


254
00:19:18,257 --> 00:19:21,792
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT TO BE HERE.   
I CAME BY TO PAY MY RESPECTS,   


255
00:19:21,861 --> 00:19:24,695
    AND THE COOK CALLED IN SICK,
    SO I OFFERED TO HELP.       


256
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:27,965
            YOU WOULD HAVE DONE 
            THE SAME THING.     
WHAT DO YOU WANT?               


257
00:19:28,968 --> 00:19:31,569
        A TRUCE WOULD BE NICE.  


258
00:19:31,637 --> 00:19:37,308
    <i> LOOK, LIEUTENANT, I KNOW</i>   
    <i> WE HAVEN'T GOTTEN OFF</i>      
    <i> TO A VERY GOOD START.</i>      


259
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:41,445
        I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW 
        THAT I UNDERSTAND HOW   
        YOU MUST BE FEELING.    


260
00:19:41,514 --> 00:19:45,582
            REALLY?             
        <i> TAMARA COPELAND</i>        
        <i> WAS YOUR BEST FRIEND.</i>  


261
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:48,653
            I'M NOT TRYING      
            TO TAKE HER PLACE.  


262
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:51,121
        I JUST WANNA DO MY JOB. 


263
00:19:52,925 --> 00:19:55,493
GRAB THOSE PLATES, WOULD YOU?   


264
00:19:59,499 --> 00:20:02,867
        YOU'RE NOT GONNA        
        MAKE THIS EASY, ARE YOU?
WHAT?                           


265
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:04,868
                ME HATING YOU.  


266
00:20:07,907 --> 00:20:10,340
            - THANKS, NANCY.    
            -<i> SEE YOU LATER.</i>    


267
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:13,076
        I WORRY ABOUT THAT GIRL.


268
00:20:13,145 --> 00:20:17,214
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?               
        IT SEEMS LIKE SHE CAN'T 
        LET GO OF WHAT HAPPENED.


269
00:20:17,283 --> 00:20:21,152
    IT FEELS LIKE SHE BLAMES    
    HERSELF FOR TAMARA'S DEATH. 


270
00:20:24,691 --> 00:20:26,657
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT, WASN'T IT?  


271
00:20:27,694 --> 00:20:30,261
            MY DAUGHTER WAS     
            A GREAT FIREFIGHTER.


272
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:32,630
    AND I LOVED HER MORE THAN   
    ANYTHING IN THIS LIFE.      


273
00:20:34,067 --> 00:20:36,901
        BUT SHE KNEW THIS WAS   
        DANGEROUS WORK,         


274
00:20:36,970 --> 00:20:39,069
            AND PEOPLE DIE.     


275
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:43,307
            I GOTTA GO CHECK ON 
            THE MEATBALLS.      


276
00:20:57,156 --> 00:21:00,090
BROOTS, ANOTHER                 
POSSIBILITY FROM ANGELO.        


277
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:15,472
                SYDNEY, BROOTS. 


278
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:19,443
I'M CONFIDENT IT'S              
A LANDLOCKED STATE, EITHER      
PENNSYLVANIA OR WEST VIRGINIA.  


279
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,615
THIS ISN'T AN EXACT SCIENCE.    


280
00:21:24,683 --> 00:21:28,552
IT'S AN EXPERIMENTAL            
TECHNIQUE WITH A HUGE           
HUMAN ELEMENT INVOLVED.         


281
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:32,289
            BEEN UP ALL NIGHT,  
            HAVEN'T YOU?        
UH-HUH.                         


282
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:35,226
    LET ME GET YOU SOME COFFEE. 


283
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:37,695
        MAYBE THAT MIGHT HELP.  


284
00:21:48,574 --> 00:21:52,076
OH, MAN.                        
WHO BROUGHT THAT DAMN MUTT?     
                    GUILTY, SIR.


285
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:54,812
WELL, KEEP HIM OUT              
OF THE HOUSE, WILL YOU?         


286
00:21:54,881 --> 00:21:57,548
            HEY, HANK.          
            OFF WITH THE SHOES. 
            HOUSE RULES.        


287
00:21:57,617 --> 00:22:01,285
<i>THAT ITALIAN SLATE COST ME</i>      
<i>$20 A SQUARE FOOT TO PUT IN.</i>    


288
00:22:01,353 --> 00:22:03,720
        YOU HEARD ABOUT A KING  
        IN HIS CASTLE?          


289
00:22:03,789 --> 00:22:06,657
BETWEEN THAT MUTT               
AND THESE SLOBS,                
I'M GONNA HAVE TO BUILD A MOAT. 


290
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:09,260
    CAP'S A REGULAR BOB VILA.   
    HE BUILT THE BAR.           


291
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:11,662
        I'M GONNA BUILD         
        A GARAGE THIS SUMMER.   


292
00:22:11,730 --> 00:22:13,797
A REMODEL THIS BEAUTIFUL        
HAS TO BE EXPENSIVE.            


293
00:22:13,866 --> 00:22:16,299
        WELL, THERE'S           
        A LOT OF SWEAT EQUITY.  
<i>[ Roy ] YEAH.</i>                   


294
00:22:16,368 --> 00:22:19,303
- OUR SWEAT, HIS EQUITY.        
- CHECK THE HAMBURGERS, ROY.    


295
00:22:19,372 --> 00:22:23,107
    <i> AND DON'T LET 'EM BURN.</i>    


296
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:27,445
GOOD KID. CAN'T HANDLE          
A BELT SANDER TO SAVE HIS LIFE, 
BUT HE'S A GOOD KID.            


297
00:22:28,781 --> 00:22:32,649
        YOU KNOW, THIS RAILING--
        1934 LADDER TRUCK.      


298
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:35,152
    THE VERY FIRST ONE          
    THE FIGHTING 16th EVER HAD. 


299
00:22:35,221 --> 00:22:39,489
    HARRIGAN'S USED THAT RAILING
    A LOT, AND I DON'T MEAN     
    IN THE LINE OF DUTY.        


300
00:22:39,558 --> 00:22:41,825
[ Chuckling ]                   
                    <i> YOU KNOW,</i>  


301
00:22:41,894 --> 00:22:44,128
YOU LANDED YOURSELF             
IN A VERY SPECIAL UNIT, JAROD.  


302
00:22:44,197 --> 00:22:46,497
HISTORICAL IS MORE LIKE IT.     


303
00:22:46,566 --> 00:22:49,766
THIS IS THE FIRST UNIT          
IN THE CITY WITH TWO            
FEMALE FIREFIGHTERS.            


304
00:22:49,835 --> 00:22:53,003
    YEAH, WITH GLEASON          
    AND COPELAND THERE,         
    IT FELT LIKE A REAL FAMILY. 


305
00:22:54,306 --> 00:22:58,175
NANCY MISSES                    
COPELAND VERY MUCH.             
            WE ALL DO, SON.     


306
00:22:58,244 --> 00:23:02,079
MUST'VE TAKEN A LOT             
OF GUTS FOR COPELAND TO RUN     
INTO THAT BURNING WAREHOUSE.    


307
00:23:02,148 --> 00:23:05,116
    <i> YEAH, ELECTRICAL FIRE</i>      
    <i> LIKE THAT.</i>                 


308
00:23:05,184 --> 00:23:08,619
    THAT PLACE MUST'VE BEEN     
    HOTTER THAN SATAN'S ARMPIT. 


309
00:23:08,688 --> 00:23:14,625
    <i> COPELAND WAS GOOD,</i>         
    <i> BUT SHE HAD AN OVERZEALOUS</i> 
    <i> SENSE OF THE HEROIC.</i>       


310
00:23:14,694 --> 00:23:17,028
I TOLD EVERYBODY TO HANG BACK.  


311
00:23:17,096 --> 00:23:19,663
SHE THOUGHT SHE HEARD SCREAMS   
AND WENT INSIDE HALF-COCKED.    


312
00:23:19,732 --> 00:23:22,599
REALLY? THAT WASN'T             
IN THE PAPERS.                  


313
00:23:22,668 --> 00:23:24,869
    <i> COPELAND DID OUTSTANDING</i>   
    <i> WORK ON THIS TEAM.</i>         


314
00:23:24,937 --> 00:23:29,339
I WASN'T ABOUT TO LET HER       
BE DISGRACED OVER ONE MISTAKE.  


315
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:34,177
    <i> I CALLED THE HOSE CREW IN</i>  
    <i> TO BRING IN A LINE</i>         
    <i> AND WENT IN AFTER HER.</i>     


316
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:37,515
    BY THE TIME I GOT INSIDE,   
    SHE WAS SUCKED INTO         
    THE SMOKE AND FLAMES.       


317
00:23:38,651 --> 00:23:41,585
    - I NEVER FOUND HER.        
    - THAT WAS VERY BRAVE.      


318
00:23:43,523 --> 00:23:46,524
        TRUTH IS, BRAVERY HAD   
        NOTHING TO DO WITH IT.  


319
00:23:46,592 --> 00:23:50,694
    AS LONG AS I'M IN CHARGE,   
    THIS TEAM WILL NEVER LEAVE  
    ONE OF ITS OWN HANGING.     


320
00:24:06,579 --> 00:24:09,245
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO ACCEPT THIS 
AS A PASSING GOOD MOOD, ARE YOU?


321
00:24:09,314 --> 00:24:12,682
            I KNOW YOU TOO WELL.
DON'T BE SO SURE.               


322
00:24:12,751 --> 00:24:14,684
            BUT I'M CONCERNED.  


323
00:24:14,753 --> 00:24:17,554
            MR. PATRICK SEEMS   
            AWFULLY TRANSIENT.  


324
00:24:17,623 --> 00:24:21,225
WHAT I DO FOR RECREATION        
IS MY BUSINESS.                 


325
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:23,226
BESIDES, I LIKE HIM.            


326
00:24:23,295 --> 00:24:25,796
        ASK YOURSELF THIS THEN. 


327
00:24:25,864 --> 00:24:29,767
        ARE THERE ENOUGH        
        HEALTHY RELATIONSHIPS   
        IN YOUR LIFE...         


328
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:33,104
    TO COMPENSATE FOR WHAT      
    YOU'RE DOING FOR RECREATION?


329
00:24:33,172 --> 00:24:36,807
            THESE ENTANGLEMENTS?


330
00:24:36,876 --> 00:24:39,476
THEY'RE NOT FREE FROM EMOTIONAL 
REPERCUSSIONS, YOU KNOW.        


331
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:44,481
LET ME GIVE YOU A NICKEL'S WORTH
OF FREE ADVICE, SYD.            


332
00:24:44,550 --> 00:24:46,917
YOU ONLY KNOW AS MUCH ABOUT ME  
AS I WANT YOU TO KNOW.          


333
00:24:46,985 --> 00:24:49,653
AND YOUR CONCERN,               
THOUGH TOUCHING--               


334
00:24:49,721 --> 00:24:54,058
<i>[ Cups Clink ]</i>                  
IS WASTED ON ME.                


335
00:24:58,030 --> 00:25:00,096
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT, JAROD.      


336
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:03,166
THIS IS THE BEST MEAL           
WE'VE HAD AROUND HERE IN MONTHS.
OH, THANKS.                     


337
00:25:03,235 --> 00:25:06,570
    SO HOW DID YOU BECOME       
    MARTHA STEWART OVERNIGHT?   


338
00:25:06,639 --> 00:25:09,273
    INSTA-CHEEZ.                
                    [ Chuckles ]


339
00:25:09,342 --> 00:25:13,177
ACTUALLY, IT WAS AN OLD RECIPE  
OF TAMARA COPELAND'S.           


340
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:22,686
EXCUSE ME.                      
        NANCY, I--              


341
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:28,459
    OH, MAN. I WAS TRYING       
    TO DO SOMETHING GOOD.       


342
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:30,461
                I THINK YOU DID.


343
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:35,199
    I THINK COOKING ONE         
    OF COPELAND'S MEALS HELPS   
    TO KEEP HER HERE AMONG US.  


344
00:25:35,268 --> 00:25:40,037
-WE DON'T WANNA EVER FORGET HER.
-NO, WE SURE DON'T.             


345
00:25:40,106 --> 00:25:43,140
<i>- [ Young Sydney ]</i>              
<i>  WHAT ARE YOU SEEING, JAROD?</i>   
- I'M NOT SURE.                 


346
00:25:43,209 --> 00:25:45,809
THINK, JAROD.                   


347
00:25:45,878 --> 00:25:48,812
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?              
FOCUS ON THE FACES.             


348
00:25:51,117 --> 00:25:55,619
THESE PEOPLE,                   
SOME ARE ANGRY, SOME ARE SAD.   


349
00:25:55,688 --> 00:25:58,455
- BUT ALL FOR THE SAME REASON.  
- AND THAT IS?                  


350
00:25:58,524 --> 00:26:02,760
    THEY WERE BETRAYED BY AMIN. 
    HE KILLED HIS OWN PEOPLE.   


351
00:26:02,828 --> 00:26:05,795
YES, AND?                       


352
00:26:05,864 --> 00:26:08,465
        THEY COULD NO LONGER    
        TRUST THEIR OWN LEADER. 


353
00:26:23,082 --> 00:26:25,049
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>WHAT ARE YOU SEEING, JAROD?</i>     


354
00:26:27,219 --> 00:26:29,686
<i>WHAT DOES IT MEAN?</i>              


355
00:26:30,856 --> 00:26:33,157
<i>THINK, JAROD.</i>                   


356
00:26:33,225 --> 00:26:35,526
<i>WHAT DOES IT MEAN?</i>              


357
00:27:35,621 --> 00:27:38,521
[ Aerosol Spraying ]            
                    <i> [ Whining ]</i>


358
00:27:40,693 --> 00:27:42,626
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>NOTHING LIKE</i>                    
<i>A GRINDER AT HERB'S.</i>            


359
00:27:42,694 --> 00:27:47,130
        NOW THAT WILL GET YOU   
        TALKING TO YOURSELF.    
THEY ARE GOOD.                  


360
00:27:47,199 --> 00:27:51,467
            SO, YOU BUYING ME   
            A TURKEY SANDWICH.  


361
00:27:51,536 --> 00:27:53,470
    IF YOU'RE HOPING            
    TO GET LUCKY, YOU'RE NOT.   


362
00:27:53,539 --> 00:27:56,306
LUCKY?                          


363
00:27:56,375 --> 00:28:00,210
                    IT'S A JOKE.
OH.                             


364
00:28:00,279 --> 00:28:02,312
WELL, I WAS HOPING I MIGHT      
ASK YOU A FEW QUESTIONS.        


365
00:28:02,381 --> 00:28:04,314
                    FIGURES.    
YOU SEE,                        


366
00:28:04,383 --> 00:28:07,784
I'M TRYING TO GET A GRASP       
ON THIS BURN PATTERN THING.     


367
00:28:07,853 --> 00:28:13,623
AND I HAVE A BET WITH ROY       
THAT THIS WAS AN ACCIDENTAL     
ELECTRICAL FIRE.                


368
00:28:13,692 --> 00:28:17,827
            YEAH, WELL,         
            YOU BETTER PAY HIM. 
REALLY?                         


369
00:28:17,896 --> 00:28:20,630
WHY IS THAT?                    


370
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:25,869
SEE THE CHAR TRAIL LEAD         
FROM THE MIDDLE OF THE ROOM,    
TRAVELS OUT IN A WEB PATTERN?   


371
00:28:25,937 --> 00:28:29,473
        ALL THE FLAMES ARE BELOW
        THE ELECTRICAL FIXTURES.


372
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:31,741
        IT'S A PLANNED TORCHING.


373
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:33,743
                    ARSON.      


374
00:28:33,813 --> 00:28:35,979
    YOU GONNA EAT THAT PICKLE?  


375
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:39,950
SO IF IT WAS RULED              
AN ELECTRICAL FIRE--            


376
00:28:40,019 --> 00:28:41,985
    WHOEVER DID IT WAS A MORON. 


377
00:28:42,053 --> 00:28:44,154
            HMM.                


378
00:28:44,222 --> 00:28:47,824
WELL, I GUESS THAT MORON        
WOULD HAVE TO BE YOU.           


379
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:53,329
<i>BECAUSE IT WAS YOUR RULING FROM</i> 
<i>THE TRI-RIVER WAREHOUSE FIRE.</i>   


380
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:56,133
YOU REMEMBER THE ONE.           


381
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:03,173
SHE DIED                        
IN IT TRYING TO SAVE YOUR LIFE. 


382
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:05,508
            YOU DON'T KNOW      
            WHAT YOU'RE SAYING. 


383
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:08,979
<i>I KNOW YOU CHECKED INTO</i>         
<i>ST. JOE'S HOSPITAL</i>              
<i>THE NIGHT SHE DIED...</i>           


384
00:29:09,047 --> 00:29:12,515
WITH A THIRD-DEGREE BURN        
ON YOUR BACK.                   


385
00:29:12,585 --> 00:29:17,688
<i>AND I ALSO KNOW THAT HARRIGAN</i>   
<i>LET THREE OTHER WAREHOUSE FIRES</i> 
<i>BURN TO THE GROUND.</i>             


386
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:20,457
<i>FIRES THAT YOU RULED ACCIDENTAL.</i>


387
00:29:20,525 --> 00:29:22,692
INSURANCE PAYOFFS.              


388
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:25,194
IS THAT WHY SHE'S DEAD?         


389
00:29:27,266 --> 00:29:29,032
<i>[ Herb ]</i>                        
<i>GENTLEMEN.</i>                      


390
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:34,037
    - HOW DO YOU LIKE           
      THOSE SANDWICHES?         
    - THEY WERE TERRIFIC.       


391
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:40,577
-HOW MUCH DO WE OWE YOU?        
-HEY, YOUR MONEY'S NO GOOD HERE.
 YOU GUYS ARE FAMILY.           


392
00:29:49,755 --> 00:29:52,423
[ Zimmerman ]                   
AN EMPTY WAREHOUSE GOES UP,     


393
00:29:52,491 --> 00:29:54,791
A MINI-MALL GETS BUILT.         


394
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:59,163
    [ Jarod ]                   
    INSURANCE PAYS FOR IT ALL.  
    NOBODY GETS HURT.           


395
00:29:59,231 --> 00:30:02,399
THAT'S THE WAY IT WORKED        
UNTIL THAT NIGHT.               


396
00:30:02,468 --> 00:30:05,469
[ Sighs ]                       
ALL I HAD TO DO WAS...          


397
00:30:05,538 --> 00:30:09,173
SPREAD AN ALCOHOL-BASED         
PROPELLANT AROUND THE FLOOR...  


398
00:30:09,241 --> 00:30:13,477
AND BUST A COUPLE OF PIPES,     
MAKE IT LOOK ELECTRICAL.        


399
00:30:13,546 --> 00:30:16,012
ONCE THE FIRE WAS BURNING       
STEADY, I STARTED TO            
BEAT IT OUT OF HERE,            


400
00:30:16,082 --> 00:30:20,551
BUT MY KNEE GAVE OUT,           
AND I COULDN'T HARDLY MOVE.     


401
00:30:20,619 --> 00:30:22,652
                IS THAT HOW     
                YOU GOT BURNED? 


402
00:30:22,721 --> 00:30:24,854
        YEAH.                   


403
00:30:24,923 --> 00:30:27,124
FLAMES WERE EVERYWHERE.         


404
00:30:27,193 --> 00:30:31,195
THEY CAUGHT MY SHIRT.           
THE DAMN PAIN WAS SO BAD,       
I MUST'VE LET OUT A SHRIEK.     


405
00:30:31,263 --> 00:30:34,364
    TAMARA COPELAND HEARD YOU.  
<i>YEAH.</i>                           


406
00:30:39,304 --> 00:30:43,706
BUT THE SMOKE WAS SEARING       
MY LUNGS, AND I COLLAPSED,      


407
00:30:43,775 --> 00:30:46,075
<i>AND I THOUGHT I WAS</i>             
<i>A GONER FOR SURE.</i>               


408
00:30:46,144 --> 00:30:50,947
<i>THEN I LOOKED UP AND SAW HER</i>    
<i>EMERGING THROUGH THE FIRE.</i>      


409
00:30:51,016 --> 00:30:54,450
    SHE MUST'VE RECOGNIZED YOU. 
<i>YEAH.</i>                           


410
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:59,756
SHE KNEW I'D DONE THIS,         
BUT IT DIDN'T STOP HER.         


411
00:31:00,993 --> 00:31:04,527
SHE JUST WENT ABOUT HER JOB.    


412
00:31:06,864 --> 00:31:10,400
INSTEAD OF SAVING HER OWN LIFE, 


413
00:31:11,736 --> 00:31:13,970
SHE STARTED TO SAVE MINE.       


414
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:16,639
    AND THEN HARRIGAN CAME IN.  


415
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:21,477
HE HIT HER WITH A CROWBAR.      


416
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:23,680
TOLD ME TO GET AWAY.            


417
00:31:23,748 --> 00:31:26,148
SAID HE WASN'T                  
GOING DOWN FOR THE FIRE.        


418
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:31,520
<i>HE TOOK HER OXYGEN AND HANDED</i>   
<i>IT OVER LIKE IT WAS NOTHING.</i>    


419
00:31:31,589 --> 00:31:34,490
            ALL SHE WANTED TO DO
            WAS SAVE YOUR LIFE. 


420
00:31:37,829 --> 00:31:40,196
INSTEAD SHE DIED                
IN THAT FIERY HELL.             


421
00:32:01,219 --> 00:32:02,719
                    JAROD.      


422
00:32:02,788 --> 00:32:04,954
<i>[ Miss Parker Chuckles ]</i>        


423
00:32:12,463 --> 00:32:14,530
                        PARKER. 
        WHAT?                   


424
00:32:16,367 --> 00:32:19,135
    ARE WE EVER GONNA MAKE IT   
    TO YOUR BEDROOM?            


425
00:32:19,204 --> 00:32:22,038
[ Both Laughing ]               


426
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:27,343
GETTING THERE IS HALF THE FUN.  


427
00:32:27,412 --> 00:32:30,079
                [ Phone Rings ] 
                DON'T.          


428
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:32,081
I HAVE TO.                      


429
00:32:33,584 --> 00:32:37,220
                        WHAT?   
        WE HAVE A CONFIRMED HIT,
        MISS PARKER.            


430
00:32:38,390 --> 00:32:40,956
            ANGELO?             
OH, THE GUY'S AMAZING.          


431
00:32:41,025 --> 00:32:42,958
HE NARROWED IT DOWN             
TO FIVE CLIPPINGS.              


432
00:32:43,027 --> 00:32:46,195
THE WINNER'S A PLACE CALLED     
THE BORODIN SMOKE HOUSE         
IN PITTSBURGH.                  


433
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:48,264
THEY CONFIRMED THAT JAROD       
WAS THERE UNTIL RECENTLY,       


434
00:32:48,333 --> 00:32:50,499
AND HIS TRAIL IS                
PROBABLY STILL HOT.             


435
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:53,736
BORODIN SMOKE HOUSE, PITTSBURGH.


436
00:32:53,805 --> 00:32:56,105
GET SYDNEY ON THE HORN          
AND GET TRANSPORTATION READY.   
I'LL BE RIGHT OVER.             


437
00:32:56,173 --> 00:32:58,841
            YES, MA'AM.         


438
00:33:04,749 --> 00:33:07,250
        PRETTY FAMILY.          


439
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:11,787
<i>TIME TO GO SEE THEM.</i>            
<i>YOUR BUSINESS TRIP JUST ENDED.</i>  


440
00:33:19,097 --> 00:33:22,498
<i>[ Knocking On Door ]</i>            
                        YEAH?   


441
00:33:22,567 --> 00:33:24,533
LIEUTENANT.                     
                        YEAH.   


442
00:33:24,603 --> 00:33:27,570
CAN I SHOW YOU SOMETHING?       
            SURE, COME ON IN.   


443
00:33:33,078 --> 00:33:35,411
        THIS IS A DUTY ROSTER.  


444
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,714
FROM THE NIGHT                  
THAT TAMARA COPELAND DIED.      


445
00:33:43,221 --> 00:33:45,588
    IF THAT'S SOME SICK JOKE,   
    IT'S NOT FUNNY.             


446
00:33:45,657 --> 00:33:48,057
        AND IF IT'S A REMINDER, 
        I DO NOT NEED ONE.      


447
00:33:48,126 --> 00:33:51,193
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO WORK       
THE SHIFT THE NIGHT SHE DIED.   


448
00:33:51,262 --> 00:33:53,730
BUT SHE FILLED IN               
FOR YOU, DIDN'T SHE?            


449
00:33:58,169 --> 00:34:00,202
        IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN ME. 


450
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:04,674
I KNOW THAT YOU FEEL THAT WAY.  


451
00:34:04,743 --> 00:34:07,543
BUT MAYBE YOU COULD             
ALLOW YOURSELF TO SEE           
THE OTHER SIDE OF THE COIN.     


452
00:34:12,917 --> 00:34:14,851
    THEY'RE MORE DUTY ROSTERS.  


453
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:17,686
FROM SHIFTS YOU FILLED IN       
FOR HER OVER THE YEARS.         


454
00:34:19,924 --> 00:34:21,857
<i>NANCY.</i>                          


455
00:34:21,926 --> 00:34:25,995
WE ALL KNOW THE RISKS.          
YOU CAN'T BLAME YOURSELF.       


456
00:34:27,498 --> 00:34:30,099
        I WASN'T THERE FOR HER. 


457
00:34:31,770 --> 00:34:34,837
MAYBE YOU FEEL YOU WEREN'T THERE
FOR HER THAT NIGHT.             


458
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:38,408
BUT YOU CAN BE THERE            
FOR HER NOW.                    


459
00:35:05,771 --> 00:35:08,938
THAT JAROD VRONSKY              
WAS A GODSEND.                  


460
00:35:09,007 --> 00:35:13,309
I DIDN'T THINK                  
WE WERE GOING TO SURVIVE        
AFTER MY FATHER DIED.           


461
00:35:14,712 --> 00:35:17,046
        DID JAROD LEAVE         
        ANYTHING BEHIND?        


462
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:19,048
OH, HE INCREASED PRODUCTIVITY,  


463
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:24,453
RESTRUCTURED OUR                
INVESTMENT STRATEGY             
AND ORGANIZED A DENTAL PLAN.    


464
00:35:24,522 --> 00:35:29,392
ALL HE ASKED IN RETURN          
WAS TO SIT IN THERE.            


465
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:32,829
    NOW WHY WOULD STEPFORD BOY  
    WANT TO SIT IN A SMOKEHOUSE?


466
00:35:32,898 --> 00:35:34,830
<i>JAROD THINKS IN METAPHORS.</i>      


467
00:35:34,899 --> 00:35:39,936
        HE COULD BE ANYTHING    
        FROM SMOKE JUMPER TO    
        SIDESHOW FIRE-EATER.    


468
00:35:40,004 --> 00:35:41,937
OH, HE LOVED SMOKE.             


469
00:35:42,007 --> 00:35:45,641
SAID HE WANTED IT               
IN HIS PORES.                   
                <i> MR. BORODIN.</i>   


470
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:49,612
DID JAROD LEAVE ANYTHING BEHIND,
LIKE A RED NOTEBOOK?            


471
00:35:49,681 --> 00:35:52,047
SAME AS BEFORE.                 
I DON'T HAVE IT.                


472
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:54,217
            "SAME AS BEFORE"?   
I HAVE HAMS TO STOW.            


473
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:58,221
            [ Speaking Russian ]


474
00:36:05,730 --> 00:36:07,830
I GAVE IT TO THE OTHER MAN.     


475
00:36:07,899 --> 00:36:10,700
                    WHO?        
A MAN CAME HERE                 
LESS THAN AN HOUR AGO.          


476
00:36:10,769 --> 00:36:12,701
HE KNEW MANY THINGS             
ABOUT JAROD.                    


477
00:36:12,770 --> 00:36:17,807
HE SAID THAT THE OTHERS         
WOULD COME. THE OTHERS THAT     
WOULD WANT TO HURT JAROD.       


478
00:36:17,875 --> 00:36:21,343
        <i> BROOTS IS THE ONLY</i>     
        <i> OTHER ONE WHO KNOWS.</i>   


479
00:36:23,215 --> 00:36:25,281
        [ Cell Phone Ringing ]  


480
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:27,282
                        WHAT?   
            [ Broots ]          
            UH, MISS PARKER.    


481
00:36:28,453 --> 00:36:32,154
                I GOT HIM.      
                I KNOW EXACTLY  
                WHERE JAROD IS. 


482
00:36:41,833 --> 00:36:44,166
OKAY, EMBER.                    
IT'S SHOWTIME.                  


483
00:36:45,970 --> 00:36:48,471
            COME ON.            
            YOU CAN DO IT.      


484
00:36:48,539 --> 00:36:51,407
            - IT'S EASY.        
            - [ Whines ]        


485
00:37:14,132 --> 00:37:16,365
                COME ON,        
                YOU CAN DO IT.  


486
00:37:16,434 --> 00:37:18,467
                    IT'S EASY.  


487
00:37:18,536 --> 00:37:20,469
                    WATCH.      


488
00:37:23,475 --> 00:37:25,841
                LIKE THIS.      


489
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:32,415
COME ON,                        
YOU CAN DO IT. COME ON.         


490
00:37:32,483 --> 00:37:34,584
            - [ Whines ]        
            - COME ON.          


491
00:37:46,030 --> 00:37:48,164
        EMBER, COME ON.         


492
00:37:48,233 --> 00:37:50,699
        COME ON.                
         COME ON, BOY.          


493
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,812
                [ Whines ]      


494
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:06,315
            [ Barks ]           


495
00:38:11,723 --> 00:38:15,725
        <i> [ Chatter, Indistinct ]</i>


496
00:38:19,730 --> 00:38:22,364
        ANYBODY SEEN ZIMMERMAN? 
        HE'S BEEN PAGING ME     
        ALL AFTERNOON.          


497
00:38:22,433 --> 00:38:24,366
            YEAH, HE JUST       
            PULLED OUT OF HERE. 


498
00:38:24,436 --> 00:38:26,869
            HE LOOKED KIND OF   
            STRANGE, EXCITED.   


499
00:38:26,938 --> 00:38:30,640
HE SAY WHERE HE WAS GOING?      
    NO. OH, HE LEFT YOU THIS.   


500
00:38:41,486 --> 00:38:45,721
    - ANYTHING WRONG, CAP?      
    - NO.                       


501
00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:51,093
<i>[ Harrigan ]</i>                    
<i>ZIMMERMAN?</i>                      
<i>YOU HERE, ZIMMERMAN?</i>            


502
00:39:08,113 --> 00:39:10,179
WHY, YOU LITTLE BASTARD.        


503
00:39:12,984 --> 00:39:15,785
            HARRIGAN.           


504
00:39:16,787 --> 00:39:18,920
IS THIS ANY WAY TO TREAT A DOG? 


505
00:39:18,989 --> 00:39:22,825
- WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?  
- I WANNA SHOW YOU THIS NEAT    
  TRICK I TAUGHT EMBER.         


506
00:39:22,894 --> 00:39:24,927
I DON'T CARE ABOUT              
THAT STUPID MUTT. UNCUFF ME.    
                    HEY.        


507
00:39:24,995 --> 00:39:28,163
        HE'S NOT STUPID.        
        HE'S MAN'S BEST FRIEND, 
        YOU KNOW.               


508
00:39:28,232 --> 00:39:30,900
AND I'VE LEARNED THAT           
IF YOU JUST KEEP HIM WELL FED,  


509
00:39:30,969 --> 00:39:33,202
        HE'LL DO JUST ABOUT     
        ANYTHING FOR YOU.       


510
00:39:33,271 --> 00:39:37,773
<i>HIS FOOD OF CHOICE,</i>             
<i>AS IS YOURS, IS INSTA-CHEEZ.</i>    


511
00:39:37,842 --> 00:39:41,043
    IT'S NOT VERY GOOD FOR YOU, 
    BUT, WHAT THE HEY,          
    IT DOES TASTE GOOD.         


512
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:44,079
O'LEARY, IF I GET OUT OF HERE,  
I'M GONNA BREAK YOUR NECK.      


513
00:39:44,148 --> 00:39:48,116
THEN I BETTER NOT LET YOU OUT.  
NOW, ABOUT THAT TRICK.          


514
00:39:48,185 --> 00:39:50,253
<i>[ Aerosol Spraying ]</i>            


515
00:39:50,321 --> 00:39:54,590
    EMBER, LIGHT THIS PLACE UP. 


516
00:39:54,658 --> 00:39:57,727
                COME ON, BOY.   
                 COME ON.       


517
00:40:01,032 --> 00:40:03,999
            <i> GOOD BOY.</i>          
            <i> NEAT LITTLE TRICK,</i> 
            <i> HUH, HARRIGAN?</i>     


518
00:40:04,068 --> 00:40:06,602
    <i> BUT WATCH, THERE'S MORE.</i>   


519
00:40:08,005 --> 00:40:12,041
- WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?  
<i>- OOPS, ELECTRICAL FIRE.</i>        


520
00:40:12,109 --> 00:40:14,843
            STARTED BY A DOG.   
            TERRIBLE ACCIDENT.  


521
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:18,013
    - PUT IT OUT!               
    -<i> I'D LIKE TO,</i>              
    <i>  BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW.</i>     


522
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:20,816
    YOU SEE,                    
    I'M NOT REALLY A FIREMAN.   


523
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:23,119
<i>OOPS, THERE GOES ANOTHER ONE.</i>   


524
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:26,755
TAKE THE DAMN CUFFS OFF ME NOW! 
    <i> CAN'T.</i>                     
    <i> GOTTA MAKE A PHONE CALL.</i>   


525
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:33,095
        <i> [ Touchtones Beeping ]</i> 


526
00:40:33,164 --> 00:40:35,397
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               
COMPANY 16.                     


527
00:40:35,466 --> 00:40:37,400
[ Jarod ]                       
I'D LIKE TO REPORT              
A FIRE, PLEASE.                 


528
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:43,673
16309 ELLSWORTH TERRACE.        


529
00:40:43,741 --> 00:40:45,674
    THANK YOU.                  


530
00:40:45,743 --> 00:40:49,344
    - [ Ringing ]               
    - [ Beeping ]               


531
00:40:51,616 --> 00:40:55,250
        WELL, I SURE HOPE       
        THAT THE FIGHTING 16th  
        GETS HERE ON TIME.      


532
00:40:55,319 --> 00:40:58,353
    THE FLAMES ARE SPREADING    
    PRETTY FAST IN THESE WALLS. 


533
00:40:59,524 --> 00:41:01,791
            <i> BUT THAT'S NOT</i>     
            <i> REALLY A SURPRISE.</i> 


534
00:41:01,859 --> 00:41:05,427
YOU SEE, I'VE TREATED           
THE WIRING THROUGHOUT THE HOUSE 
WITH THIS ACCELERANT.           


535
00:41:05,496 --> 00:41:08,464
THAT WAY THE FLAMES             
AND THE FIRE SPREAD COMPLETELY. 


536
00:41:08,532 --> 00:41:12,334
AND IT LOOKS LIKE AN ACCIDENT.  
NO ONE WILL EVER KNOW.          


537
00:41:12,403 --> 00:41:16,171
WHAT ABOUT ME?                  
    <i> WELL, EVEN THE BEST</i>        
    <i> ARSONISTS MAKE MISTAKES--</i>  


538
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:18,374
<i>[ Flames Building ]</i>             
            DON'T THEY, CHIEF?  


539
00:41:19,377 --> 00:41:21,977
OH, NO!                         


540
00:41:22,046 --> 00:41:24,546
GIVE ME THE KEY!                
        HE LOOKS PRETTY SCARED, 


541
00:41:24,615 --> 00:41:26,348
        DOESN'T HE, EMBER?      


542
00:41:26,417 --> 00:41:31,587
I BET TAMARA COPELAND           
LOOKED PRETTY SCARED TOO        
THE NIGHT OF THE TRI-RIVER FIRE.


543
00:41:31,655 --> 00:41:33,655
        BUT SHE HAD YOU THERE   
        TO BACK HER UP.         


544
00:41:33,724 --> 00:41:37,226
            <i> SOMEONE SHE TRUSTED</i>
            <i> TO PROTECT HER.</i>    


545
00:41:38,429 --> 00:41:40,662
        GO WAIT OUTSIDE, EMBER. 


546
00:41:40,731 --> 00:41:43,699
<i>-I'D HATE TO SEE YOU GET BURNED.</i>
<i>-[ Sirens Approaching ]</i>         


547
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:53,843
    LIEUTENANT!                 
                <i> HOLD IT, GUYS.</i> 


548
00:41:53,911 --> 00:41:56,011
        THERE'S SOMETHING       
        YOU NEED TO KNOW FIRST. 


549
00:41:57,581 --> 00:42:01,750
[ Jarod ]                       
I'VE GOT TO GO NOW. IT'S        
GETTING PRETTY STUFFY IN HERE.  


550
00:42:07,091 --> 00:42:09,425
        O'LEARY, YOU CAN'T      
        LEAVE ME HERE TO BURN!  


551
00:42:09,493 --> 00:42:13,929
WHY NOT? YOU LEFT               
TAMARA COPELAND, DIDN'T YOU?    


552
00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:16,665
            YES, I LEFT HER!    
<i>YOU LEFT HER TO BURN.</i>           


553
00:42:16,733 --> 00:42:18,601
SO YOU COULD COLLECT            
THE PAYOFF MONEY.               


554
00:42:18,669 --> 00:42:21,037
        SO YOU COULD BUY        
        THIS ITALIAN SLATE TILE.


555
00:42:21,105 --> 00:42:25,307
OR THAT 1934 LADDER TRUCK       
RAILING AROUND YOUR WET BAR     
THAT YOU'RE SO PROUD OF.        


556
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:28,644
YES, I LEFT HER.                
NOW, GIVE ME THE KEY, PLEASE.   


557
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,981
        - THIS KEY?             
        - YEAH.                 


558
00:42:32,050 --> 00:42:34,549
    SURE.                       


559
00:42:39,290 --> 00:42:41,557
HOPE YOU DON'T BURN.            


560
00:42:41,625 --> 00:42:46,529
            <i> O'LEARY! O'LEARY!</i>  


561
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:53,902
            [ Screaming ]       


562
00:42:55,873 --> 00:42:57,806
            MY HOUSE!           


563
00:42:57,875 --> 00:43:00,542
THAT SON OF A BITCH             
BURNED MY HOUSE!                


564
00:43:00,612 --> 00:43:02,911
    PUT IT OUT.                 
     PUT IT OUT!                


565
00:43:02,981 --> 00:43:04,913
    HANG BACK.                  


566
00:43:04,983 --> 00:43:08,084
THIS PLACE IS DEFINITELY N.W.S. 


567
00:43:08,152 --> 00:43:12,354
    COME ON, GUYS.              
    I BUILT THAT HOUSE.         
    DON'T LET IT BURN LIKE THAT.


568
00:43:12,423 --> 00:43:14,723
        I'M YOUR CAPTAIN.       
         I'M YOUR DAMN CAPTAIN! 


569
00:43:16,327 --> 00:43:18,861
            TO HELL WITH YOU.   


570
00:43:33,511 --> 00:43:36,011
<i>[ Glass Shattering ]</i>            


571
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:55,231
            YOU MUST BE JAROD.  
            <i> [ Gun Cocks ]</i>      


572
00:44:01,105 --> 00:44:03,772
        - WHO ARE YOU?          
        - [ Chuckles ]          


573
00:44:03,841 --> 00:44:07,009
        UH, YOU'RE REALLY NOT   
        IN A POSITION TO ASK.   


574
00:44:09,279 --> 00:44:12,815
        NOW PUT YOUR HANDS UP   
        AND TURN AROUND.        


575
00:44:21,292 --> 00:44:23,993
                    [ Barking ] 


576
00:44:32,103 --> 00:44:35,270
GOOD-BYE. GOOD-BYE.             


577
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:37,506
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.            


578
00:44:37,574 --> 00:44:40,775
I HAVE TO GO.                   
IT WAS VERY NICE TO MEET YOU.   


579
00:44:49,453 --> 00:44:52,221
        [ Miss Parker ]         
        YOU COVER THE BACK.     
        EVERYONE ELSE WITH ME.  


580
00:45:03,367 --> 00:45:05,267
        WHO'RE YOU WORKING FOR? 


581
00:45:05,336 --> 00:45:07,769
            I TOLD YOU, PARKER. 


582
00:45:07,839 --> 00:45:10,238
        I'M A SALES REP FOR A-- 


583
00:45:10,307 --> 00:45:13,675
                OH, YOU BITCH!  


584
00:45:13,744 --> 00:45:16,979
        YOU DON'T KNOW          
        THE HALF OF IT.         
        WHO'RE YOU WORKING FOR? 


585
00:45:17,047 --> 00:45:19,248
        ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.   
        THE CENTRE.             


586
00:45:20,884 --> 00:45:23,786
                MR. RAINES.     


587
00:45:25,789 --> 00:45:29,624
DON'T, PARKER. DON'T.           
THERE MIGHT BE REPERCUSSIONS.   


588
00:45:33,731 --> 00:45:35,397
            [ Groaning ]        


589
00:45:38,269 --> 00:45:41,069
                BY THE WAY,     
                I WAS FAKING IT.


590
00:45:51,849 --> 00:45:53,782
HEY, I CAN'T EAT THIS.          


591
00:45:53,851 --> 00:45:56,985
I WOULDN'T GIVE                 
THAT CRAP TO MY DOG.            
            OH, NO PROBLEM.     


592
00:45:57,054 --> 00:45:59,154
            I CAN FIX THAT.     


593
00:46:08,065 --> 00:46:09,999
            <i> BON APPÉTIT.</i>       


594
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:43,799
            [ Mews ]            


